📌 Basic GitHub (Git) Commands – Brief Notes
🔹 git init

Initializes a new Git repository in the current folder

Creates a hidden .git directory

git init

🔹 git status

Shows the current state of the working directory

Displays tracked, untracked, and modified files

git status

🔹 git add

Adds files to the staging area

git add file.txt     # add specific file
git add .            # add all files

🔹 git commit

Saves staged changes with a message

git commit -m "Initial commit"

🔹 git log

Displays commit history

git log

🔹 git branch

Lists, creates, or deletes branches

git branch           # list branches
git branch dev       # create branch

🔹 git checkout

Switches between branches or commits

git checkout dev


(Modern alternative: git switch dev)

🔹 git merge

Merges one branch into another

git merge dev

🔹 git remote

Manages remote repositories

git remote -v

🔹 git clone

Creates a local copy of a remote repository

git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git

🔹 git pull

Fetches and merges changes from remote repo

git pull origin main

🔹 git push

Uploads local commits to remote repository

git push origin main

🔹 git fetch

Downloads changes without merging

git fetch

🔹 git reset

Removes files from staging area or resets commits

git reset file.txt

🔹 git rm

Deletes file from working directory and repo

git rm file.txt

🔹 git diff

Shows differences between changes

git diff

🧠 Git Workflow (Exam Gold ⭐)
Working Directory
   ↓ git add
Staging Area
   ↓ git commit
Local Repository
   ↓ git push
Remote Repository (GitHub)